metadata.title: Bell 206
aws::graph::propositions: Military Variants of Bell 206 Helicopter
206L TexasRanger was a proposed export military version of the Bell 206.
One 206L TexasRanger demonstrator was built in 1981.
TH-57B helicopters were commercial Bell 206B-3 helicopters purchased by the US Navy.
The US Navy purchased 45 TH-57B helicopters in 1989.
TH-57B helicopters replaced the TH-57A helicopters.
TH-57B helicopters were used for primary training under visual flight rules.
TH-57C Sea Ranger helicopters were commercial Bell 206B-3 helicopters purchased by the US Navy.
The US Navy purchased 71 TH-57C Sea Ranger helicopters.
The US Navy began purchasing TH-57C Sea Ranger helicopters prior to 1985.
TH-57C Sea Ranger helicopters had cockpits configured for advanced training under instrument flight rules.
TH-57D was a planned upgrade program for US Navy helicopters.
TH-57D program aimed to convert US Navy TH-57B and TH-57C aircraft to a single standard digital cockpit.
The TH-57D program never materialized in operational aircraft.
TH-67 Creek helicopters were commercial Bell 206B-3 helicopters.
The US Army purchased 137 TH-67 Creek helicopters in 1993.
TH-67 Creek helicopters served as the primary and instrument helicopter trainer for the US Army.
TH-67 Creek helicopters were used at Fort Novosel, Alabama.
Bell 206 helicopters were used by Navy helicopter pilots.
Bell 206 helicopters were used by U.S. Marine Corps helicopter pilots.
Bell 206 helicopters were used by U.S. Coast Guard helicopter pilots.
Bell 206 helicopters were used by select NATO helicopter pilots.
Bell 206 helicopters were used by select Allied helicopter pilots.

text:
Navy, U.S. Marine Corps, U.S. Coast Guard and select NATO/Allied helicopter pilots.

206L TexasRanger
proposed export military version. One demonstrator was built (1981).
TH-57B
45 commercial Bell 206B-3 helicopters purchased by the US Navy in 1989 as replacements for the TH-57A for primary training under visual flight rules.
TH-57C Sea Ranger
71 commercial Bell 206B-3 helicopters purchased by the US Navy beginning prior to 1985 with cockpits configured for advanced training under instrument flight rules.
TH-57D
Planned upgrade program to convert US Navy TH-57B and TH-57C aircraft to a single standard digital cockpit. This program never materialized in operational aircraft.
TH-67 Creek
137 commercial Bell 206B-3s purchased in 1993 as the primary and instrument helicopter trainer for the US Army at Fort Novosel, Alabama.
